caption: This was 'Blood Swept Lands and Seas of Red', an art installation at the Tower of London consisting of 888,246 ceramic poppies - one for each British and Colonial soldier who died during the war. It commemorated the 100th year since Britain's first day in the First World War. The first poppy was planted on the 5th August, with the 888,246th poppy being planted on 11th November 2014. Each of the poppies was sold to charity raising millions for six associated charities. It is now 105 years since the armistice was signed between the Allies and Germany, ceasing a war in which an estimated 37,000,000 people died. #remembranceday #toweroflondon
